snippet.title: Amber Heard can't stop smiling as she steps out holding hands with new girlfriend Bianca Butti
snippet.description:
Thanks for watching my video.

For any copyright, please send me a message. AMBER Heard appeared loved up during a recent outing with new girlfriend Bianca Butti.  The actress, 33, looked head over heels in love as she held hands with the cinematographer at the 2020 Women's March in Downtown Los Angeles.   Amber was one of many celebrities addressing crowds at the March at Pershing Square on Saturday.  The star kept it casual in a simple black t-shirt, jeans and stacked gold necklaces.  She also sported an ankle book on her injured leg.  Meanwhile, Bianca, who is currently fighting a second breast cancer diagnosis, wore an all-black ensemble of skinny jeans, a bomber jacket and a t-shirt.    During the day, Amber took to the stage to discuss the many issues affecting women in the US and beyond.  She appeared passionate as she read out her speech as a American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) ambassador.  Amber and Bianca were first spotted sharing a kiss outside a hotel in Palm Springs earlier this week.  It's unknown how long the pair have been dating for.   The Aquaman star was previously married to fellow actor Johnny Depp.  She met Johnny after they both starred in The Rum Diary in 2011 and began living together the following year.  They married at a private civil ceremony at their home in LA on February 3, 2015.  However just 15 months later Amber filed for divorce and it was finalised in January 2017.    Got a story? email digishowbiz@the-sun.co.uk or call us direct on 02077824220.  We pay for videos too.
